LORE ashborn
FLAGS ASHBORN
Living consequence of the Ashfall Era; bodies incorporated Cinderteeth
volcanic material instead of dying from it; the transformation is heritable
Skin: smooth bronze through rough stone-gray to fractured black-and-orange
(cooling lava crust); mineral deposits at joints and along forearms
Injuries seal in mineral crust that must be cracked away as tissue heals;
elevated body temperature; exposed tissue may glow faint orange
Heavier than apparent size: significant mineral deposits in bones and
subcutaneous tissue; built for sustained effort, not agility
Immune to volcanic particulate toxicity; can operate in Cinderteeth approach
zones that kill unprotected travelers
A young people; some have living elders who remember being unmodified
Spirebound Conclave's Ember Canon doctrine was possibly influenced by
observing early Ashborn; deliberate attempts to replicate the transformation
failed — it required the specific Ashfall conditions, not controlled fire
~
